Use Case:
1. I write a post in a [HAML/Markdown] file.
2. I Commit the file and push to GitHub.
3. I run some sort of script on my app to let it know that I've added a new post. It checks out a copy of that file and creates a post entry in the DB and starts showing the post.

Alternative Use Case
1. I write a post ing a [HAML/Markdown] file.
2. I commit the file to my git repo and push directly to Heroku with the necessary changes in the DB. No update required.

TBK:
1. Investigate: Heroku's DB system.
2. Markdown parser in Ruby
